# Supabase Configuration
# Get these values from your Supabase project dashboard:
# Settings > API

EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here

# ===========================================
# GOOGLE NATIVE AUTH SETUP
# ===========================================
#
# You need THREE OAuth Client IDs from Google Cloud Console:
# 1. Web Client ID (required for Supabase)
# 2. iOS Client ID (for native iOS sign-in)
# 3. Android Client ID (for native Android sign-in)
#
# STEP 1: Create a Google Cloud Project
# --------------------------------------
# 1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com
# 2. Create a new project or select existing one
# 3. Enable the "Google Identity" API
#
# STEP 2: Configure OAuth Consent Screen
# ---------------------------------------
# 1. Go to APIs & Services > OAuth consent screen
# 2. Choose "External" user type
# 3. Fill in app name, user support email, developer contact
# 4. Add scopes: email, profile, openid
# 5. Add test users if in testing mode
#
# STEP 3: Create OAuth Client IDs
# --------------------------------
# Go to APIs & Services > Credentials > Create Credentials > OAuth Client ID
#
# A) Web Application (REQUIRED for Supabase)
#    - Name: "Faynman AI Web"
#    - Authorized JavaScript origins: https://your-project-id.supabase.co
#    - Authorized redirect URIs: https://your-project-id.supabase.co/auth/v1/callback
#    - Copy the Client ID below:
EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_WEB_CLIENT_ID=your-web-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com

# B) iOS Application
#    - Name: "Faynman AI iOS"
#    - Bundle ID: com.faynmanai.app (must match app.json bundleIdentifier)
#    - Copy the Client ID below:
EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_IOS_CLIENT_ID=your-ios-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com

# C) Android Application
#    - Name: "Faynman AI Android"
#    - Package name: com.faynmanai.app (must match app.json package)
#    - SHA-1 certificate fingerprint: Get this by running:
#      cd android && ./gradlew signingReport
#      (or use: keytool -list -v -keystore ~/.android/debug.keystore -alias androiddebugkey -storepass android -keypass android)
#    - Copy the Client ID (not needed in env, but create it for Android to work)

# STEP 4: Configure Supabase
# --------------------------
# 1. Go to Supabase Dashboard > Authentication > Providers > Google
# 2. Enable Google provider
# 3. Enter your Web Client ID and Web Client Secret
# 4. Save

# STEP 5: Update app.json
# -----------------------
# Replace "YOUR_IOS_CLIENT_ID" in app.json plugins section with your actual iOS Client ID:
# The format should be: com.googleusercontent.apps.YOUR_IOS_CLIENT_ID
# Example: com.googleusercontent.apps.123456789-abcdefg.apps.googleusercontent.com

# STEP 6: Rebuild the app
# -----------------------
# After configuration, rebuild your app:
# npx expo prebuild --clean
# npx expo run:ios (or run:android)
